result.execSummary:
Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.
result.caption: State of Wisconsin vs. Suzzette L. Burnett

records.addlTxt:
Defendant Suzzette L. Burnett in court.  Attorney Michael C Turner in court for Suzzette L. Burnett.  Prosecuting attorney Jordan W. Feest in court for the State of Wisconsin. 
State moves to dismiss and read in this file as part of a plea agreement with 21CF990, 21CF989, 21CF894, 22CF483 and 22CF491.  Motion granted.
Order Denying Defendant's Motion to Modify Bail.

BAIL MODIFICATION:  Defendant is wishing to have the no contact provision modified from no contact to no assaultive contact with J.B. in 21CF894, 21CF419, 22CF190 and 21CF990.  The Court is taking the position that case nos. 22CF483 and 22CF491 are a result of Defendant violating the no contact provision.  Court therefore denies the modification at this time until further documentation is provided that the modification request is mutual.  Defense counsel will continue to secure such documentation.  Attorney Feest to prepare order. 
Additionally, Defendant wishes to have the cash bail converted to signature bond in 22CF491.   Counsel makes argument for a reduction or conversion of the cash bond.  State is objecting to a reduction based on past performance while on bond and feels that the current cash bail is appropriate.  Court finds that a reduction of the $500.00 cash bail is not appropriate at this time.  Attorney Feest to prepare order. 
Scheduling conference scheduled for September 30, 2022 at 03:30 pm.
Scheduling conference on July 20, 2022 at 11:30 am.
Scheduling conference on June 8, 2022 at 10:30 am.

1:58 p.m.  Defendant waives her right to a preliminary hearing.  Defendant is bound over to Circuit Court Branch 3 for trial.

Not guilty plea(s) entered.  Jury calendar.
Offer deadline:  5/6/22, 8:30 a.m.
Minutes.

Prior: Manitowoc County Jail, Manitowoc, WI 54220

2:40 pm - Prosecuting attorney Jordan W. Feest appeared in court for the State of Wisconsin, Defendant Suzzette L. Burnett appeared by video, in custody, Attorney Michael C Turner appeared by video for Suzzette L. Burnett. Defendant demands a preliminary hearing. 
MOTION TO MODIFY BAIL - 
Attorney Turner requests bail be modified to $5,000.00 recognizance bond.  Attorney Feest objects to the modification.  Defendant has 5 open felony cases which involve the same victim and missed appearances.
The Court orders bail modified from cash to $5,000.00 recognizance bond with the condition that she have no assaultive contact with J.B.  Bail furnished.
Preliminary hearing scheduled for March 23, 2022 at 01:30 pm.
